CODE:
# Original string 
original_string = "python 3.0" 
 
# Convert the string to a tuple of characters 
char_tuple = tuple(original_string) 
 
# Print the original string's class type 
print("Original string:", original_string) 
print("Class type of the original string:", type(original_string)) 
 
# Print the converted tuple 
print("Convert the said string to a tuple:", char_tuple) 
print("Class type of the converted tuple:", type(char_tuple))

OUTPUT: 
Original string: python 3.0 
Class type of the original string: <class 'str'> 
Convert the said string to a tuple: ('p', 'y', 't', 'h', 'o', 'n', ' ', '3', 
'.', '0') 
Class type of the converted tuple: <class 'tuple'> 
